SIMPLE: pudding
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pudding
<hw>Pud"ding</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>boudin</ets> black pudding, sausage, L. <ets>botulus</ets>,
<ets>botellus</ets>, a sausage, G. & Sw. <ets>pudding</ets> pudding,
Dan. <ets>podding</ets>, <ets>pudding</ets>, LG. <ets>puddig</ets>
thick, stumpy, W. <ets>poten</ets>, <ets>potten</ets>, also E.
<ets>pod</ets>, <ets>pout</ets>, v.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A species of
food of a soft or moderately hard consistence, variously made, but often
a compound of flour or meal, with milk and eggs, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And solid <qex>pudding</qex> against empty praise.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Anything resembling, or of the softness and
consistency of, pudding.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>An intestine; especially, an intestine stuffed with
meat, etc.; a sausage.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Any food or victuals.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Eat your <qex>pudding</qex>, slave, and hold your tongue.</q>
<rj><qau>Prior.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>Same as
<er>Puddening</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<cs><p><col><b>Pudding grass</b></col> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>, <cd>the true
pennyroyal (<spn>Mentha Pulegium</spn>), formerly used to flavor
stuffing for roast meat.</cd> <au>Dr. Prior.</au> -- <col><b>Pudding
pie</b></col>, <cd>a pudding with meat baked in it.</cd> <au>Taylor
(1630).</au> -- <col><b>Pudding pipe</b></col> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>,
<cd>the long, cylindrical pod of the leguminous tree <spn>Cassia
Fistula</spn>. The seeds are separately imbedded in a sweetish pulp. See
<er>Cassia</er>.</cd> -- <col><b>Pudding sleeve</b></col>, <cd>a full
sleeve like that of the English clerical gown.</cd> <au>Swift.</au> --
<col><b>Pudding stone</b></col>. <fld>(Min.)</fld> <cd>See
<er>Conglomerate</er>, <pos>n.</pos>, 2.</cd> -- <col><b>Pudding
time</b></col>. <sd>(a)</sd> <cd>The time of dinner, pudding being
formerly the dish first eaten.</cd> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<au>Johnson.</au> <sd>(b)</sd> <cd>The nick of time; critical time.</cd>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Mars, that still protects the stout,⟦br⟧
In <qex>pudding time</qex> came to his aid.</q>
<rj><qau>Hudibras.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p></cs>

<p><ent>Pudding wife</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Pudding fish</ent>⟦br⟧
